#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""hapax-quota-telemetry-writer — live per-provider quota/resource telemetry.

Phase 0.4 (the designed R3 slice) of
REQ-20260609-model-capability-cost-routing-operationalization: the dispatcher's
quota state must come from live telemetry written on a timer, not from the
checked-in ``config/quota-spend-ledger-fixtures.json`` snapshot.

Each tick does two writes:

1. Refresh the per-provider platform capability receipts (quota / resource /
   capability surfaces) via ``scripts/hapax-platform-capability-receipts --all``.
   The registry freshness check reads these; the quota surface carries
   ``stale_after=15m``, so the paired systemd timer fires inside that window to
   keep subscription routes from HOLDing on ``quota_telemetry_stale_or_unknown``.

2. Rebuild the live quota/spend ledger at
   ``~/.cache/hapax/orchestration/quota-spend-ledger-live.json`` (or
   ``$HAPAX_QUOTA_SPEND_LEDGER_LIVE``). Governance records (transition budgets,
   spend receipts, dependencies, provenance, renewals) are carried over from the
   checked-in base unchanged — telemetry never grants spend authority. The
   telemetry fields are re-derived live:

   - ``captured_at``: now.
   - subscription ``quota_snapshots``: per-platform state from the quota-wall
     relay receipts (``~/.cache/hapax/relay/receipts/<role>-quota-wall.yaml``,
     written by ``shared.quota_wall`` on observed 429/quota-exhaustion). An
     unexpired wall marks the platform ``exhausted``; otherwise the established
     Claude/Codex/Gemini subscription routes are ``fresh``. GLMCP is stricter:
     it is ``unknown`` unless a fresh, short-lived admission receipt exists.
     Coding Plan quota walls block Coding Plan receipts, but a fresh
     endpoint-matched PAYG admission can supersede that subscription wall only
     when it is bound to the active Coding Plan quota-wall witness.
     Recheck admission evidence with
     ``find ~/.cache/hapax/relay/receipts -maxdepth 1 -name '*glmcp-quota-admission*.yaml' -print``
     and ``scripts/hapax-quota-telemetry-writer --json``.
     If a receipt exists but GLMCP remains ``unknown``, read this writer's
     stderr warnings; malformed, stale, mismatched, or unbounded receipts are
     ignored loudly.
     Admission receipts with ``stale_after_seconds`` above 3600 seconds are
     intentionally ignored; write a fresh short-lived witness instead.
     The emergency false-negative recovery path is to create a fresh
     short-lived admission receipt with schema, status, provider, capacity_pool,
     route_id, supported_tool, endpoint, model, observed_at, stale_after_seconds,
     evidence_ref, and explicit no-secret/no-content/billing fields, then rerun
     this writer so the live ledger is refreshed.
     That receipt-plane refresh is the canonical emergency procedure for a
     false negative.
     There is intentionally no environment-variable bypass for stale/unknown
     subscription quota. ``evidence_ref`` values are limited to 3-240 safe
     witness-reference characters.
   - ``local_resource_state`` + local-compute snapshot: nvidia-smi VRAM
     pressure and load average, fail-closed to ``unknown`` when unprobeable.

The output is validated through ``QuotaSpendLedger.model_validate`` before an
atomic replace, so a bad tick can never clobber a good live ledger with junk.
No secrets are read or persisted: the probes are local files, nvidia-smi, and
the existing receipts script (which records config paths/existence only).
"""

